💳 NEXUS ATM is a fully-featured desktop banking simulation application written in 🐍 Python, developed by me. It mimics a real-world 🏧 Automated Teller Machine (ATM) with a graphical user interface (GUI) 🖥️ built using the Tkinter library, which comes bundled with Python's standard library.

🔐 The program lets users log in with an account number and PIN, then perform real banking operations:
💰 deposit money, 💸 withdraw cash, 🔄 transfer funds between accounts, 📊 view transaction history, 🔑 manage their PIN, and more.
All data is saved to 📁 JSON files on disk so balances and transactions are remembered between sessions.

🧠 It is also an excellent demonstration of Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) principles, clean code organisation, use of Python data structures, input validation ✅, and GUI development 🎨 — all in a single self-contained file.
